@startuml

title FX Atomic Swap via a Shared ERC-20 Settlement Router\nExample: Party A receives BASE_QTY base tokens and pays QUOTE_QTY quote tokens

autonumber
hide footbox
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

actor "Deployer" as Deployer
actor "Party A\n(inceptor)" as PartyA
actor "Party B\n(confirmer)" as PartyB
participant "FxAtomicSwapFactory" as Factory
participant "ERC20SettlementRouter\n(common spender)" as Router
participant "FxAtomicSwap\n(single-use swap)" as Swap
participant "Base ERC-20" as BaseToken
participant "Quote ERC-20" as QuoteToken

== Factory and settlement router deployment ==

Deployer -> Factory ++ : new FxAtomicSwapFactory()
create Router
Factory -> Router ++ : new ERC20SettlementRouter(address(Factory))
Router -> Router : factory = Factory\n(immutable)
Router --> Factory -- : router deployed
Factory -> Factory : settlementRouter = Router\n(immutable)
Factory --> Deployer -- : factory deployed

== ERC-20 allowances ==

note over PartyA, QuoteToken
Allowances are given early to the deployed settlementRouter.
Swaps created though the FxAtomicSwapFactory will settle though the settlementRouter.
end note

PartyA -> QuoteToken ++ : approve(Router, quoteAllowance)
QuoteToken -> QuoteToken : allowance[PartyA][Router] = quoteAllowance
QuoteToken --> PartyA -- : true

PartyB -> BaseToken ++ : approve(Router, baseAllowance)
BaseToken -> BaseToken : allowance[PartyB][Router] = baseAllowance
BaseToken --> PartyB -- : true

note over PartyA, QuoteToken
For this sign configuration, Party A authorizes quote-token spending
and Party B authorizes base-token spending. The approvals can be reused
across all swaps registered with the same router.
end note

== Creation and one-time authorization ==

PartyA -> Factory ++ : createSwap(BaseToken, QuoteToken, PartyA, PartyB)
Factory -> Factory : require caller is PartyA or PartyB
create Swap
Factory -> Swap ++ : new FxAtomicSwap(\n  BaseToken, QuoteToken, PartyA, PartyB, Router\n)
Swap -> Swap : store immutable tokens, parties, and Router\nphase = Created
Swap --> Factory -- : swap address
Factory -> Router ++ : registerSwap(Swap)
Router -> Router : require msg.sender == Factory\nactiveSwap[Swap] = true
Router --> Factory -- : registered
Factory --> PartyA -- : Swap address\nSwapCreated

note over Swap, Router
The router stores only one active flag per swap.
The swap is the single source of tokens, parties, and terms.
end note

== ERC-6123 inception by Party A ==

PartyA -> Swap ++ : inceptTrade(\n  PartyB, tradeData,\n  +BASE_QTY, -QUOTE_QTY, settlementData\n)
Swap -> Swap : validate fixed parties\nvalidate nonzero, opposite-sign legs
Swap -> Swap : inceptor = PartyA\nposition = +BASE_QTY\npaymentAmount = -QUOTE_QTY\nstore textual terms\nphase = Incepted
Swap --> PartyA -- : tradeId = "1"\nTradeIncepted

note right of Swap
Sign convention from the inceptor's perspective:
  position > 0       => receive base
  paymentAmount < 0  => deliver quote
end note

== ERC-6123 confirmation and atomic settlement ==

PartyB -> Swap ++ : confirmTrade(\n  PartyA, same tradeData,\n  -BASE_QTY, +QUOTE_QTY, same settlementData\n)
Swap -> Swap : verify counterparty, negated amounts, and terms
Swap -> Swap : phase = Settled\n(checks-effects-interactions)
Swap -> Router ++ : settleAtomicSwap(\n  BaseToken, QuoteToken, PartyA, PartyB,\n  +BASE_QTY, -QUOTE_QTY\n)

note over Swap, Router
Inside the router, msg.sender = Swap.
The one-time flag authenticates the factory-created caller.
end note

Router -> Router : require activeSwap[Swap]\nactiveSwap[Swap] = false

note right of Router
Consuming the flag before token calls prevents the same swap
from settling twice, including through a callback.
A global reentrancy lock is unnecessary for independent swaps.
end note

group Base leg: Party B delivers base to Party A
    Router -> BaseToken ++ : transferFrom(PartyB, PartyA, BASE_QTY)
    note over Router, BaseToken
    Inside BaseToken, msg.sender = Router.
    Therefore allowance[PartyB][Router] is used.
    end note
    BaseToken -> BaseToken : check allowance and balance\nupdate balances and allowance
    BaseToken --> Router -- : true
end

group Quote leg: Party A delivers quote to Party B
    Router -> QuoteToken ++ : transferFrom(PartyA, PartyB, QUOTE_QTY)
    note over Router, QuoteToken
    Inside QuoteToken, msg.sender = Router.
    Therefore allowance[PartyA][Router] is used.
    end note
    QuoteToken -> QuoteToken : check allowance and balance\nupdate balances and allowance
    QuoteToken --> Router -- : true
end

Router --> Swap -- : settlement completed
Swap -> Swap : emit TradeConfirmed\nemit TradeTerminated
Swap --> PartyB -- : confirmation transaction succeeds

note over PartyA, QuoteToken
All calls occur within Party B's single confirmation transaction.
If validation or either transferFrom fails, the transaction reverts
atomically: both token transfers and both state changes are undone.
end note

@enduml
